<B>Company Information:</B><BR>
Since 1989, Fujitsu General has been a leader in plasma display technology.
Beginning with the introduction of the first color plasma monitor in 1993,
the Plasmavision 21, Fujitsu General has been the front-runner in
commercialization of plasma display technology.  The Plasmavision 42, first
introduced in January 1997, was the world's first large-format, flat-panel
plasma display and garnered many awards, including the prestigious Technical
Excellence Award from PC Magazine.  Today, Fujitsu General's full line
includes one of the thinnest self-contained HD plasma displays currently
offered in the world.  Now available, the PDS-4222 has a cabinet depth of
3.3 inches and inclusive weight of only 69 pounds.  Fujitsu General proudly
offers the complete 42-inch display solution for the consumer market.
